Entry.JapaneseText: ケケット街道沿いの小屋
ケケット街道沿いの小屋
い、いらっしゃいましぇ!!
<speed:00><scale:0140> 泊まる 世間話をする やめる
泊まってってくださいよー。
なんか身体中が痛い…… 筋肉痛みたいな痛さなんです……
Entry.EnglishText: My body hurts all over... I've got muscle pains...

Entry.JapaneseText: まるで誰かと 力比べしたみたいな……
Entry.EnglishText: It's as if my mind went through a power struggle with another person...

Entry.JapaneseText: ここケケット街道沿いの小屋の 「眠眠亭」はお客様に愛されて、 はや五十年です。
Entry.EnglishText: Keketto Highroad Hostel's "Goodnight's Sleep" has been loved by its customers for over 50 years.

Entry.JapaneseText: 最近、赤字ぎみですが、 おじいさんの始めた店を 潰すわけにはいきません！
Entry.EnglishText: Even though we've been losing money lately, we can't afford to lose the store my grandfather started!

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e000040><Veigue>、 鐘じゃないようだ。 他の音を探すんだ。
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000040><Veigue>, it doesn't seem to be the bell. Try some other sound.

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00003f><Veigue>、 それじゃないみたいだよ。 早く、他の音を探して!!
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00003F>It's not that. Hurry and try another sound!

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00003b><Mao>の寝息が、 暗示のきっかけだったの かもしれない……
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00003B>Maybe the sound of <Mao>'s breathing when he was asleep triggered the hypnosis?

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00003c>ボクの寝息？ だとしたら夜の間に 何かあったはずだよ。
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00003C>My breathing? If that were the case, wouldn't this have happened during the night?

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00003d>だって寝てる間は ずっと寝息を立てる ものでしょ？
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00003D>I'm pretty sure you're supposed to breath the whole time you're asleep.

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00003e><Veigue>、 音の出そうなものを探すんだ！ 手当たり次第に音を立てろ！
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00003E><Veigue>, find something that can make noise! Use whatever you can get your hands on!

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e000008>三名様ですね。 ごゆっくりどうぞ。
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000008>Three customers, I see. Please enjoy your stay.

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00000b><Claire>さんの事が 気になっているのか？
<voice:0e00000d>寝ておけ……と言っても 眠れるものではないかも しれないな。
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00000D>I would tell you to get some sleep, but I know that's easier said than done.

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00000e>だが、どんな状況だろうと 眠れるようにしておくんだ。 後々がつらくなるぞ。
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E00000E>But no matter what you're going through, you need to be able to get some rest. Things are going to be tough from here on out.

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e000011>もうこんな時間か。 そろそろ行こう。
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000011>We're off to a late start. Let's get going.

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e000016>……七つの力を…… ボクは目……ボクは……
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000016>...the Power of the Seven... I am the Eye... I am...
<voice:0E000017>The Power of the Seven... What's that supposed to mean?

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e000018>……いつもこの調子だ…… もしかしたら、失ったはずの記憶を 夢に見ているのではないかと 思っているんだが……
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000018>...This happens all the time. I wonder if it's because he sees his lost memories in his dreams, but...

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e00001f>でも、フォルスは感じないよ？
<voice:0e000020>だが、あの動きは 普通じゃなかった。 <Blue>王の盾<White>の能力者か？
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000020>But his movements were too precise. Could he be from the Royal Shield?

Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000043>Hm...the clock? Come to think of it...

Entry.JapaneseText: <voice:0e000048>安心するのは まだ早いみたいだね…… 近いよ。外だ!!
Entry.EnglishText: <voice:0E000048>We can't relax just yet. He's close by... Let's go outside!
